Johannesburg – Former Mamelodi Sundowns spokesperson Thulani Thuswa is no more. Thuswa, who left the club last year, died this morning in a car accident. Multiple sources who spoke to Sunday World said that Thuswa was driving home from celebrating the club’s league victory with the Brazilians coaches at Melrose Arch when he lost control of his luxury vehicle on N1 north near Malboro off rand and hit an embankment. He died instantly. Also read: Revealed: Sundowns contract restricted Mosimane’s authority as coach Thuswa’s death has sent shockwaves through the football industry. This is a developing story, as more details become available, this article will be updated. Have you read: Popular Nigerian prophet TB Joshua has died Follow @SundayWorldZA on Twitter and @sundayworldza on Instagram, or like our Facebook Page, Sunday World, by clicking here for the latest breaking news in South Africa. To Subscribe to Sunday World, click here. Sunday World  